args: If my darling and I can wander the world\ntogether, I will need for nothing else.
Grant my wish, outfit of dreams!\nMake us travelers!
Oh, we're starting outside this time, eh?\nWell, that DOES suit two travelers.
A-are you all right, darling?\nDid I anger you somehow?
We're supposed to be two married\ntravelers adventuring together!
Welp, call us whatever floats your boat.
Hell, how else should I be, seein' as\nhow I was abandoned as a child and\nforced to beg for coin in the street?
(No! This isn't the darling I know!)
(Is this because I wished for us to\ngo on a journey together?)
(Have I made him endure a terrible\nupbringing just for me?)
Frankly, you're the one actin' strange.
Don't tell me ya got a fever!
'Course I am! You're the only one what's\nbeen by my side all these years.
Got through every hardship in my life\n'cause of you, so I did.
So if ya wanna say we're married,\nit's no skin off my nose.
(This version of him only has eyes for me.\nAnd yet, he's so different!)
(And what kind of a life are we\ngoing to end up leading here?)
(He's so strong! You can tell he's been\nfighting as a traveler for a long time.)
(My weapon is so very heavy...\nCurse these frail human bodies!)
Darling! Oh, you're going to PAY for that,\nyou fiend! Haaaaaah!
I'm fine as well, but only because you\ntook the blow intended for me!
I'd rather be hurt than see it\nhappen to you.
(He's gruff and tactless...\nBut he's still the same kind, selfless\n{player_name} I know!)
(I finally understand! THOSE were the\nparts of him I fell in love with!)
(I won't hesitate any longer! I'm going to\nlive out a happy married life in this world,\nwith this version of my darling!)
(And as I'm now a traveler,\nthere's only one thing for me to do!)
Just watch my back. That's good enough.
But I want to fight with you!
Glad ya feel that way, but there's no need\nfor you to be in harm's way.
If you keep throwin' yourself at fiends,\nI'll be throwin' dirt on your head soon.
But I'm fine! I'm a drago...
(No. I'm not. Now I'm just a human being\nso weak that even an attack from a pitiful\nfiend is enough to kill me.)
(Rrrr, this body is SO inconvenient!\nWhy did I have to become human?!)
...Wait a second. I WISHED for it!
Then let's make camp before\nwe lose the sun.
*sigh* It's no use. I can't sleep.
What do I want to do?\nHow do I truly wish to be?
All this time, I was jealous of humans.\nI thought that if I could be like them,\nI could marry my darling and be happy.
That's why I chose to become human\nin this world in the first place.
And yet, only my body is human\nnot my heart.
I'm still Brunhilda the Flamewyrm\nthe proud master of crimson!
Can I really throw away my pride if that's\nthe only way to have a human heart?
I don't know what I want here...
